1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,026 --> 00:01:37,812
=Episode 10=
(At Someone Else's Mercy)

3
00:01:38,770 --> 00:01:39,490
Stop the car.

4
00:01:40,728 --> 00:01:41,729
We won't make it.

5
00:01:41,729 --> 00:01:42,330
Wait a moment!

6
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:43,009
Hurry up.

7
00:01:44,289 --> 00:01:44,970
Stop the car.

8
00:01:45,289 --> 00:01:46,050
It's getting dark.

9
00:01:46,169 --> 00:01:47,330
Let's take them back.

10
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:48,070
Alright.

11
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:53,050
Hurry. It's the last bus.

12
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:53,490
Get on.

13
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:54,490
Hurry up.

14
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:55,089
Wait a second.

15
00:01:55,249 --> 00:01:56,289
- Hurry up.
- Kid, it's dangerous.

16
00:01:56,289 --> 00:01:56,850
- Hurry up.
- Hurry up.

17
00:01:56,850 --> 00:01:57,570
- Come on.
- Hurry up.

18
00:01:57,570 --> 00:01:58,570
It's the last bus. Hurry.

19
00:01:58,570 --> 00:01:59,169
Wait a moment.

20
00:01:59,410 --> 00:01:59,970
Wait a moment.

21
00:02:00,490 --> 00:02:01,490
Come on. Get on.

22
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:02,850
Get on. Hurry.

23
00:02:02,850 --> 00:02:03,490
I ate too much.

24
00:02:05,970 --> 00:02:06,690
Caught it luckily.

25
00:02:07,050 --> 00:02:07,809
Finally caught it.

26
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:09,930
Thanks to He Yuqiong.

27
00:02:11,010 --> 00:02:11,930
I'll give you that.

28
00:02:13,569 --> 00:02:15,930
I ate too much,
but we made it after all.

29
00:02:17,969 --> 00:02:19,050
What should we do for fun?

30
00:02:19,249 --> 00:02:20,569
What, you haven't had enough fun?

31
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,770
Of course. We had
such a great time together.

32
00:02:23,089 --> 00:02:24,330
When can we get together again?

33
00:02:26,330 --> 00:02:26,890
When?

34
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,010
Today was really fun.

35
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:32,170
These few hours feel like
stolen moments.

36
00:02:33,129 --> 00:02:34,330
Exciting and thrilling.

37
00:02:35,569 --> 00:02:36,569
This moment is great.

38
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:39,369
In another 20 years,

39
00:02:40,689 --> 00:02:41,409
where will we be?

40
00:02:43,689 --> 00:02:44,689
Will we remember this?

41
00:02:46,330 --> 00:02:46,830
We will.

42
00:02:46,890 --> 00:02:47,409
Definitely.

43
00:02:47,730 --> 00:02:49,089
Definitely unforgettable for life.

44
00:03:05,210 --> 00:03:06,330
What are you doing?

45
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:08,249
Why can't I lean on you?

46
00:03:08,649 --> 00:03:09,930
Xiaoming lets Bai Shu do it.

47
00:03:10,249 --> 00:03:11,529
Why not me?

48
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:12,249
What the heck?

49
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:13,689
Not friendly at all.

50
00:03:13,689 --> 00:03:14,409
Don't, okay?

51
00:03:14,490 --> 00:03:15,969
Just for a bit. Come on.

52
00:03:15,969 --> 00:03:17,450
You go stay over there.

53
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:19,170
Let me lean on you for a bit.

54
00:03:21,550 --> 00:03:22,409
- Don't come over.
- Come on.

55
00:03:22,409 --> 00:03:23,089
What the heck?

56
00:03:23,089 --> 00:03:24,170
Go sit at the back.

57
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:26,170
Stop messing around.
Sit tight. Be careful.

58
00:03:30,649 --> 00:03:33,129
(When can I play
with Xiaoming and them again?)

59
00:03:34,488 --> 00:03:36,610
(They're students
at La City Yucai High School now.)

60
00:03:38,170 --> 00:03:39,529
(I'm just from Qidaohezi.)

61
00:03:52,818 --> 00:03:53,689
(Qidaohezi, 2023
No.6 Hospital)

62
00:03:53,689 --> 00:03:55,689
Doctor, are these the medications?

63
00:03:56,050 --> 00:03:56,809
Ren Meiyan, right?

64
00:03:57,089 --> 00:03:57,610
Yes.

65
00:03:59,770 --> 00:04:01,170
Yes, these are the medications.

66
00:04:01,649 --> 00:04:03,610
Is my illness relapsing again?

67
00:04:04,170 --> 00:04:05,969
How are you feeling now?

68
00:04:09,369 --> 00:04:10,689
Just tell me the truth.

69
00:04:11,610 --> 00:04:13,610
I have a feeling. I can accept it.

70
00:04:14,409 --> 00:04:16,369
Be proactive in your treatment.

71
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,650
We'll do our best.

72
00:04:18,970 --> 00:04:19,569
Don't give up.

73
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:22,490
How much time do I have?

74
00:04:31,009 --> 00:04:31,569
What's wrong?

75
00:04:32,569 --> 00:04:35,329
Xiaoming, I want to talk to you.

76
00:04:36,490 --> 00:04:37,689
I've got court today.

77
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:39,410
I don't have much time. In a hurry.

78
00:04:39,410 --> 00:04:40,410
Say what you need to say.

79
00:04:42,809 --> 00:04:44,970
Come back to Qidaohezi sometime.

80
00:04:45,689 --> 00:04:47,730
Didn't I just come back from Qidaohezi?

81
00:04:47,730 --> 00:04:49,970
I'm busy. I don't have time to go back.

82
00:04:52,329 --> 00:04:54,449
I'd like to talk to you about Xiaofei.

83
00:04:54,730 --> 00:04:55,768
What's up with Xiaofei?

84
00:04:56,050 --> 00:04:57,050
Is he sick again?

85
00:04:57,449 --> 00:04:58,369
No.

86
00:04:59,009 --> 00:05:00,850
Can Xiaofei be with you in the future?

87
00:05:02,650 --> 00:05:03,410
What do you mean?

88
00:05:03,850 --> 00:05:06,090
Is Li not letting Xiaofei stay there?

89
00:05:06,530 --> 00:05:07,970
No.

90
00:05:08,569 --> 00:05:10,090
I'm talking about the future.

91
00:05:10,809 --> 00:05:12,249
Mom, don't say "in the future".

92
00:05:12,249 --> 00:05:14,730
When you pursue
your personal happiness in the future,

93
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:16,449
can you think more about the kids?

94
00:05:17,490 --> 00:05:19,129
You did it over and over again.

95
00:05:19,530 --> 00:05:21,689
Ren Xiaofei already struggles
to adapt to a new life.

96
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:29,110
(La City, 2004)
Xiaofei.

97
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:32,509
I found something fun for you. Open it.

98
00:05:32,769 --> 00:05:33,329
Open it.

99
00:05:36,209 --> 00:05:37,490
This is a small computer.

100
00:05:37,809 --> 00:05:40,009
Do some research.
It helps develop your brain.

101
00:05:40,449 --> 00:05:41,209
For me?

102
00:05:41,610 --> 00:05:42,129
Yes.

103
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:44,569
Hello, who is it?

104
00:05:49,209 --> 00:05:50,290
Wait. I'll come out.

105
00:05:53,569 --> 00:05:54,129
Hello?

106
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:02,290
How did you get it?

107
00:06:02,488 --> 00:06:03,249
Yuanyuan's, right?

108
00:06:03,249 --> 00:06:03,930
This is mine.

109
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:04,930
- Give it to me.
- This is mine.

110
00:06:05,009 --> 00:06:05,689
It's Yuanyuan's.

111
00:06:05,689 --> 00:06:06,410
This is mine.

112
00:06:06,410 --> 00:06:07,730
- Be good. Give me.
- This is mine.

113
00:06:08,009 --> 00:06:08,730
This is mine.

114
00:06:11,009 --> 00:06:11,930
What are you doing?

115
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:12,689
Well, this...

116
00:06:12,809 --> 00:06:13,309
Inside it...

117
00:06:14,490 --> 00:06:15,209
There's a...

118
00:06:15,209 --> 00:06:15,970
What are you doing?

119
00:06:16,689 --> 00:06:19,889
Xiaofei took Yuanyuan's Little Wonder.

120
00:06:20,209 --> 00:06:21,369
I gave it to him.

121
00:06:22,209 --> 00:06:24,490
I saw it was just mixed in
with a bunch of junk.

122
00:06:24,490 --> 00:06:25,530
I thought it was useless.

123
00:06:26,329 --> 00:06:27,449
It's not useless.

124
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:30,209
There's a digital dog
inside Yuanyuan's Little Wonder.

125
00:06:30,392 --> 00:06:31,389
Can't feed it that way.

126
00:06:31,389 --> 00:06:33,129
Feeding it like that, it'll just...

127
00:06:33,369 --> 00:06:35,209
It'll overeat!

128
00:06:35,209 --> 00:06:36,090
There's a dog in here?

129
00:06:37,009 --> 00:06:38,970
Yes. A digital dog.

130
00:06:39,449 --> 00:06:41,369
- Can't feed it that way.
- What did Xiaofei feed it?

131
00:06:41,889 --> 00:06:42,389
He...

132
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:43,889
He took...

133
00:06:44,569 --> 00:06:46,090
He was just using his hand...

134
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:56,249
You...

135
00:06:56,329 --> 00:06:56,829
You're...

136
00:06:57,689 --> 00:06:58,569
What are you doing?

137
00:06:59,249 --> 00:07:00,970
This is the cup we brought from home.

138
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:02,730
I'll do what I want. Not your problem.

139
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:05,030
See?

140
00:07:05,809 --> 00:07:07,209
Young in age but big temper.

141
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,970
Then the Little Wonder... Maybe I...

142
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:12,650
I'll just...

143
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:13,329
This is mine.

144
00:07:14,209 --> 00:07:16,290
Xiaofei, it's Yuanyuan's.

145
00:07:16,809 --> 00:07:17,889
I made a mistake.

146
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:21,329
I will buy you a new one.
Give this to me.

147
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:25,050
Sorry.

148
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,290
I'll take it back to Yuanyuan.

149
00:07:26,369 --> 00:07:27,689
If she's done, it's yours.

150
00:07:44,610 --> 00:07:46,809
Xiaoming, don't be like this.

151
00:07:54,296 --> 00:07:55,650
When I broke a cup in the past,

152
00:07:55,650 --> 00:07:57,449
the whole building
could hear you yell at me.

153
00:07:57,970 --> 00:07:59,610
You don't even dare yell at me now?

154
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:03,369
Xiaoming, stop talking.

155
00:08:17,138 --> 00:08:17,769
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

156
00:08:17,769 --> 00:08:18,449
Mr. Li,

157
00:08:19,209 --> 00:08:20,369
we notified you to come today

158
00:08:20,930 --> 00:08:22,410
to talk to you

159
00:08:23,209 --> 00:08:24,449
about Ren Meiyan's condition.

160
00:08:27,369 --> 00:08:29,730
What? Has it gotten serious?

161
00:08:30,329 --> 00:08:32,410
It's relapsed. Treat it quickly.

162
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:33,410
Doctor,

163
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:35,390
so

164
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:37,370
does she know about it?

165
00:08:38,089 --> 00:08:39,170
It's a relapse this time.

166
00:08:40,089 --> 00:08:41,410
She knew five years ago.

167
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:48,489
Fei.

168
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:56,930
Mom, Uncle Li is here.

169
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:01,720
Who are you looking for?

170
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:03,370
I'm looking for you.

171
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:05,530
I've settled the matter.

172
00:09:07,849 --> 00:09:08,890
So I'm here.

173
00:09:09,089 --> 00:09:09,729
Who are you?

174
00:09:10,329 --> 00:09:11,729
Does anyone in this room know you?

175
00:09:13,609 --> 00:09:14,569
He is Uncle Li.

176
00:09:15,170 --> 00:09:16,329
I am Uncle Li.

177
00:09:16,650 --> 00:09:17,290
Get out.

178
00:09:20,930 --> 00:09:22,209
- I said get out.
- I'll get out.

179
00:09:22,209 --> 00:09:22,969
Get out.

180
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:25,650
I can get out.

181
00:09:26,410 --> 00:09:28,609
I just don't know
where to go after I get out.

182
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:30,650
Awaiting your orders.

183
00:09:31,290 --> 00:09:32,290
I don't like you anymore.

184
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:34,370
There are people who do.

185
00:09:37,089 --> 00:09:37,650
Meiyan.

186
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:41,130
Today, I made things clear
with my ex-wife

187
00:09:41,410 --> 00:09:43,050
and our two kids.

188
00:09:43,969 --> 00:09:44,650
From now on,

189
00:09:45,770 --> 00:09:46,689
I'll be with you.

190
00:09:48,489 --> 00:09:51,050
You are my only companion

191
00:09:51,969 --> 00:09:53,010
for this lifetime.

192
00:09:55,352 --> 00:09:56,250
Where's your luggage?

193
00:09:58,290 --> 00:09:59,250
I left with nothing.

194
00:10:00,650 --> 00:10:01,689
Not even a toothbrush?

195
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:03,809
Severed ties with the past.

196
00:10:04,969 --> 00:10:06,689
You're just here freeloading?

197
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:08,449
You old geezer.

198
00:10:09,530 --> 00:10:10,809
- I'm not old.
- Don't show off!

199
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,689
Always bullying me.

200
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:17,890
I'm not freeloading.

201
00:10:22,089 --> 00:10:23,050
From now on...

202
00:10:23,809 --> 00:10:25,329
Your floor is quite slippery.

203
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:28,729
I won't let you lift a finger.

204
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:30,809
Order whatever you want to eat.

205
00:10:31,209 --> 00:10:32,449
Tell me what you want to do.

206
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:33,550
I...

207
00:10:34,209 --> 00:10:36,250
I am your AI.

208
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:38,890
Li!

209
00:10:41,209 --> 00:10:42,650
I'm here, Master.

210
00:10:43,209 --> 00:10:45,809
Just let me know if you need anything.

211
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,290
You're my princess.

212
00:10:53,209 --> 00:10:55,209
Princess? I want to be
the Empress Dowager.

213
00:10:58,809 --> 00:11:01,089
Then wouldn't I be the retired Emperor?

214
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:03,250
I can't accept that.

215
00:11:03,729 --> 00:11:06,130
You're putting me
on a pedestal in this house.

216
00:11:07,290 --> 00:11:09,209
I'm not fit to be in the ruling class.

217
00:11:09,809 --> 00:11:11,569
You're a princess.
No one is worthy of you.

218
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:14,849
I'm your soldier, your chef.

219
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:17,770
I'm also... I'm also your...

220
00:11:20,209 --> 00:11:21,130
The toilet is clogged.

221
00:11:21,449 --> 00:11:21,949
Coming.

222
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:22,790
Don't move.

223
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,089
Nobody move!

224
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,609
Your plumber is here.

225
00:11:43,729 --> 00:11:45,849
Is Uncle Li going to live with us?

226
00:11:46,209 --> 00:11:46,849
Is that okay?

227
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:50,104
Sure, he can stay in my room.

228
00:11:50,808 --> 00:11:52,930
What are you thinking?
How can he sleep with you?

229
00:12:02,089 --> 00:12:05,650
♪Roses, roses, so charming♪

230
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:08,969
♪Roses, roses, so dazzling♪

231
00:12:08,969 --> 00:12:12,609
Done. Xiaofei, check if the toilet
is unclogged.

232
00:12:12,890 --> 00:12:13,449
Go check.

233
00:12:18,089 --> 00:12:19,290
How could you do this?

234
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:21,569
Come on.

235
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:29,809
Meiyan,

236
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:33,410
you did get married
several times in this life.

237
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:37,209
But you always moved
into someone else's house.

238
00:12:37,770 --> 00:12:39,650
Can you feel at ease
in someone else's house?

239
00:12:40,569 --> 00:12:43,489
This time, I'll let you know

240
00:12:43,969 --> 00:12:48,010
what it means
to truly be yourself at home.

241
00:12:48,770 --> 00:12:52,209
I'm just the live-in husband,

242
00:12:52,809 --> 00:12:53,809
always at your service.

243
00:12:57,089 --> 00:12:58,209
I'm fine.

244
00:13:00,089 --> 00:13:02,530
It's just the kids
are suffering with me.

245
00:13:03,530 --> 00:13:06,329
Don't worry. I'll take good care of them
in the future.

246
00:13:10,738 --> 00:13:14,906
(La City, 2005)

247
00:13:16,849 --> 00:13:18,689
Xiaoming, you're back.

248
00:13:18,969 --> 00:13:19,969
Ren Xiaoming, come here.

249
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:27,170
Why are you shouting
with that loud voice of yours?

250
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:29,849
He is not home,
so you're the queen again?

251
00:13:33,809 --> 00:13:35,089
From Xiamolin's...

252
00:13:35,489 --> 00:13:37,089
You've got no right to eat anyway.

253
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,530
You should arrive this morning.
What time is it?

254
00:13:39,689 --> 00:13:41,930
It's dinner time. Where did you go?

255
00:13:42,969 --> 00:13:45,130
I went to Qidaohezi with Bai Shu.

256
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:48,250
Did you go look for that guy?

257
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:49,030
What...

258
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:51,729
No, what guy?

259
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:54,370
We went to see our junior high teacher.

260
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:55,530
Which teacher?

261
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,209
I'll call the school now.

262
00:13:57,329 --> 00:13:58,809
If you lie, I'll break your legs.

263
00:13:59,650 --> 00:14:00,969
We went to see Ms. Zhou.

264
00:14:03,489 --> 00:14:04,290
She's back?

265
00:14:06,969 --> 00:14:08,089
How did you know she left?

266
00:14:11,609 --> 00:14:14,370
I heard it when I passed your school
on an errand.

267
00:14:16,410 --> 00:14:17,130
Wait.

268
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:21,329
You... You knew and didn't tell me?

269
00:14:21,329 --> 00:14:22,410
Why are you like this?

270
00:14:22,890 --> 00:14:25,329
You usually chat away
about everyone else's business.

271
00:14:25,329 --> 00:14:26,650
You clam up at crucial times?

272
00:14:29,849 --> 00:14:31,329
What did the school teacher say?

273
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:34,689
Just said she was transferred,
not where to.

274
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:35,890
Anyway, it was urgent.

275
00:14:38,449 --> 00:14:39,890
Alright, come help peel the garlic.

276
00:14:43,489 --> 00:14:44,729
Why so many dishes?

277
00:14:45,969 --> 00:14:47,130
Are you pregnant?

278
00:14:47,609 --> 00:14:48,410
I'll hit you.

279
00:14:50,010 --> 00:14:51,930
Yuanyuan is coming over this weekend.

280
00:14:52,209 --> 00:14:53,250
Mr. Sun's picking her up.

281
00:14:55,849 --> 00:14:58,290
It's just a little fool.
Is all this fuss necessary?

282
00:14:58,569 --> 00:15:00,209
You made fried shrimp and sausage.

283
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:03,489
Just a peach would do.

284
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:04,569
Cut the crap.

285
00:15:05,089 --> 00:15:07,089
She's only staying for two days,
so be good.

286
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:09,689
Don't worry.
I'm only staying for one day.

287
00:15:10,449 --> 00:15:11,410
Wash the dishes.

288
00:15:11,689 --> 00:15:13,209
Even if she were a king's daughter,

289
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:14,890
I'd still have to put my bag down first.

290
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:16,329
Mom, I'll wash them for you.

291
00:15:16,729 --> 00:15:17,609
Not your concern.

292
00:15:34,569 --> 00:15:36,410
Mom, I'm starving.

293
00:15:37,290 --> 00:15:38,130
Hang in there.

294
00:15:40,089 --> 00:15:43,770
The little fool is just like her dad,
always making people wait at meal times.

295
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:44,750
Zip it.

296
00:15:50,329 --> 00:15:51,530
Come on, Yuanyuan.

297
00:15:51,770 --> 00:15:53,089
- Come on, Yuanyuan.
- Coming.

298
00:15:53,089 --> 00:15:53,650
Home now.

299
00:15:53,930 --> 00:15:54,430
Yuanyuan.

300
00:15:55,489 --> 00:15:56,449
Hello, there!

301
00:15:56,609 --> 00:15:58,089
Just like Snow White.

302
00:15:58,370 --> 00:15:59,930
Such pretty little shoes!

303
00:16:00,370 --> 00:16:01,890
What's that on your face?

304
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:04,770
This is an award from my dear daughter.

305
00:16:04,890 --> 00:16:05,530
Greet Ms. Ren.

306
00:16:06,489 --> 00:16:08,370
It's fine. Hurry and take a seat.

307
00:16:08,469 --> 00:16:08,969
Sit here.

308
00:16:08,969 --> 00:16:09,569
Sit here.

309
00:16:09,930 --> 00:16:10,430
Come.

310
00:16:10,930 --> 00:16:12,089
Come, sit.

311
00:16:12,089 --> 00:16:12,849
Sit down. Come on.

312
00:16:12,849 --> 00:16:13,349
Dad,

313
00:16:13,809 --> 00:16:15,530
it took Xiaoxue's spot.

314
00:16:16,569 --> 00:16:19,089
Then I will put it here.

315
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:20,290
Is that okay?

316
00:16:22,729 --> 00:16:25,089
Let Xiaoxue sit here.

317
00:16:25,336 --> 00:16:26,030
Is that okay?

318
00:16:26,530 --> 00:16:27,609
Xiaoxue, be good.

319
00:16:27,849 --> 00:16:29,969
After dinner,
I will take you out to play.

320
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:38,370
Come on. Let me hold you.

321
00:16:40,130 --> 00:16:40,689
Sit properly.

322
00:16:42,729 --> 00:16:43,890
Hurry. Come out for dinner.

323
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,290
The dishes will get cold.

324
00:16:46,930 --> 00:16:48,089
Right, let's eat then.

325
00:16:48,170 --> 00:16:48,670
Okay.

326
00:16:49,890 --> 00:16:51,329
Why holding that broken tea mug?

327
00:16:51,729 --> 00:16:53,329
Little fool wants to join at the table.

328
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:54,776
Is it worthy? Take it away.

329
00:16:55,449 --> 00:16:57,609
Exactly. Little fool isn't fit
for the table.

330
00:16:59,809 --> 00:17:01,209
Little fool, be good.

331
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:03,130
Don't make a fuss. After dinner,

332
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:04,729
I will take you to the park.

333
00:17:09,209 --> 00:17:10,249
Yuanyuan, come on.

334
00:17:11,410 --> 00:17:13,330
Have a fried prawn.

335
00:17:14,769 --> 00:17:17,969
It's not hygienic to give me food
with your own chopsticks.

336
00:17:19,370 --> 00:17:21,090
I haven't used these chopsticks yet.

337
00:17:22,009 --> 00:17:24,090
Even if they haven't been used,
it's still impolite.

338
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:25,529
My mom said,

339
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:28,090
"Use the serving chopsticks
when picking food for others."

340
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:31,969
Sorry, I didn't know.

341
00:17:33,049 --> 00:17:36,810
But what does your mom mean
by self-chopsticks?

342
00:17:37,170 --> 00:17:40,209
It's not self-chopsticks.
It's serving chopsticks.

343
00:17:41,370 --> 00:17:44,330
You need to prepare a pair of chopsticks
for public use.

344
00:17:46,009 --> 00:17:48,370
I see. I will go get them now.

345
00:17:49,009 --> 00:17:49,610
Got it.

346
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:59,090
I will use serving chopsticks
to pick food for you now.

347
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,370
No need. This is my home.

348
00:18:01,689 --> 00:18:02,810
You don't need to serve me.

349
00:18:05,930 --> 00:18:06,430
Well...

350
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:07,170
Yuanyuan.

351
00:18:08,249 --> 00:18:09,610
Meiyan, let's eat.

352
00:18:09,610 --> 00:18:10,810
Let's not pick food anymore.

353
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:12,930
We're all family. No need to pick food.

354
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:22,689
Yuanyuan, I'll eat this.

355
00:18:23,330 --> 00:18:23,830
Alright?

356
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:24,969
And I will pick one for you.

357
00:18:25,249 --> 00:18:25,810
One more.

358
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:26,969
Use the serving chopsticks.

359
00:18:27,570 --> 00:18:28,769
I don't mind my dad.

360
00:18:30,410 --> 00:18:31,209
Thank you, Dad.

361
00:18:31,489 --> 00:18:32,090
You're welcome.

362
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:57,489
Thank you, Mom.

363
00:18:57,729 --> 00:18:58,330
Thank you, Mom.

364
00:19:05,489 --> 00:19:05,989
Well...

365
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:09,209
Let's eat.

366
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:10,449
- Okay.
- Serving chopsticks.

367
00:19:13,410 --> 00:19:14,090
Come on, Xiaofei.

368
00:19:17,570 --> 00:19:19,890
This is my home.
You don't need to serve me.

369
00:19:21,370 --> 00:19:21,870
Yes.

370
00:19:24,249 --> 00:19:25,390
Xiaofei, eat now.

371
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:27,289
Mom made so much for us.

372
00:19:27,529 --> 00:19:28,029
Eat up.

373
00:19:28,410 --> 00:19:29,170
Yes, eat up.

374
00:19:32,769 --> 00:19:33,930
I'll get you some water.

375
00:19:34,229 --> 00:19:35,249
Eat more slowly.

376
00:19:35,289 --> 00:19:36,610
Don't choke, Yuanyuan.

377
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:37,650
Take your time.

378
00:19:38,489 --> 00:19:39,969
Let's finish everything today.

379
00:19:54,489 --> 00:19:56,090
Drink something. Don't choke.

380
00:20:03,650 --> 00:20:04,150
I...

381
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:07,249
Xiaofei, get Mom some food.

382
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:25,529
I've never seen you eat like this.

383
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:27,370
Wait, you...

384
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,289
Are the chopsticks washed together

385
00:20:46,289 --> 00:20:47,489
or separately?

386
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:51,009
What? Why are you
taking out your anger on me?

387
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:52,810
Throw it at whoever upset you.

388
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:00,370
Give it to me!

389
00:21:00,610 --> 00:21:01,570
Give it to me!

390
00:21:01,650 --> 00:21:02,410
Give it to me!

391
00:21:02,449 --> 00:21:03,249
Give it to me!

392
00:21:03,249 --> 00:21:03,890
It's mine.

393
00:21:04,370 --> 00:21:05,610
- Lend it to me!
- It's mine!

394
00:21:06,930 --> 00:21:07,930
Give it to me!

395
00:21:08,289 --> 00:21:09,469
- What are you doing?
- It's mine!

396
00:21:10,489 --> 00:21:11,689
Wait. Let her play with it.

397
00:21:11,689 --> 00:21:12,370
This is mine.

398
00:21:12,370 --> 00:21:14,130
I'll buy you what you want, okay?

399
00:21:14,130 --> 00:21:14,650
It's mine.

400
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:15,330
Let her play.

401
00:21:15,330 --> 00:21:16,570
- No!
- Just for a little while.

402
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:17,370
Just a while.

403
00:21:17,370 --> 00:21:17,930
This is mine.

404
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:18,890
What's wrong?

405
00:21:18,890 --> 00:21:20,410
Why are you fighting?

406
00:21:20,689 --> 00:21:23,249
Yuanyuan snatched my toy,
and Mr. Sun even helped her snatch it.

407
00:21:24,969 --> 00:21:26,969
I didn't snatch it.
I just came in and watched.

408
00:21:27,090 --> 00:21:28,090
She wanted this toy.

409
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:29,969
So I told Xiaofei,
"Let her play for a while.

410
00:21:29,969 --> 00:21:31,570
I will buy you whatever you want."

411
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:33,130
And he shouted and yelled.

412
00:21:33,529 --> 00:21:34,729
Well, I didn't snatch it.

413
00:21:35,049 --> 00:21:36,410
Why interfere in kids' matters?

414
00:21:36,529 --> 00:21:37,529
Even play favorites here.

415
00:21:37,810 --> 00:21:39,209
Yuanyuan, don't cry. Be good.

416
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:41,289
That's something boys play with.

417
00:21:41,370 --> 00:21:43,130
How about I get you a doll?

418
00:21:43,130 --> 00:21:43,729
No.

419
00:21:44,689 --> 00:21:48,090
Dad, I can trade Xiaoxue
with him for that.

420
00:21:48,090 --> 00:21:49,289
Who wants your stupid rabbit?

421
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:50,930
Did you hear that?

422
00:21:51,090 --> 00:21:52,729
Yuanyuan said she would trade Xiaoxue.

423
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:54,810
Xiaoxue is her favorite toy, right?

424
00:21:54,810 --> 00:21:56,610
She has already come this far,

425
00:21:56,610 --> 00:21:58,249
trading Xiaoxue with him for this toy.

426
00:21:58,410 --> 00:22:00,529
Just swap toys
and let her play for a while.

427
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:01,249
Well, this...

428
00:22:02,370 --> 00:22:04,209
This what?

429
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:06,330
Both sides need to agree, right?

430
00:22:06,610 --> 00:22:08,130
She's okay with it, but he's not.

431
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:10,289
How can you trade like this?
You can't snatch!

432
00:22:10,850 --> 00:22:11,350
Alright.

433
00:22:12,090 --> 00:22:14,130
Xiaofei's the older brother,
Yuanyuan's the younger.

434
00:22:14,449 --> 00:22:15,810
Shouldn't he let her have it?

435
00:22:16,130 --> 00:22:17,410
If my son gives in, it's right.

436
00:22:17,529 --> 00:22:19,209
If he doesn't, it's wrong?

437
00:22:20,370 --> 00:22:21,610
That's on your parenting.

438
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:24,289
If you teach him right,
would he be so rude at his age?

439
00:22:24,370 --> 00:22:26,090
Let's not argue
in front of children, okay?

440
00:22:26,489 --> 00:22:28,090
You teach your child, and I teach mine.

441
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:30,170
You call my son rude.
I call your daughter scheming.

442
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:32,610
You teach your children,
and I teach mine?

443
00:22:33,370 --> 00:22:35,810
So we teach them separately?
Should we live separately too?

444
00:22:35,930 --> 00:22:37,650
I didn't say that.
If you want to, I'm okay.

445
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:39,930
Are you sure about that?

446
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:40,650
Yes, I am.

447
00:22:41,249 --> 00:22:44,090
Alright, Ren Meiyan, I'll ask you again.

448
00:22:44,410 --> 00:22:46,090
Are you sure about what you just said?

449
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:47,449
Sun Jinfu, I do what I say.

450
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:48,170
Okay.

451
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:48,670
Dad.

452
00:22:53,769 --> 00:22:56,370
If Yuanyuan really likes this model,
I'll make her another one.

453
00:23:00,689 --> 00:23:01,249
Yuanyuan,

454
00:23:01,410 --> 00:23:04,090
I like this bunny. Give it to me.

455
00:23:04,729 --> 00:23:05,729
I will give you a model.

456
00:23:10,130 --> 00:23:11,224
Dad, what do you think?

457
00:23:11,969 --> 00:23:14,570
I-I think it's a good idea.

458
00:23:15,529 --> 00:23:18,289
Yuanyuan, I think
what Xiaoming said is good.

459
00:23:18,650 --> 00:23:19,850
I don't want the model.

460
00:23:20,170 --> 00:23:23,170
Stupid Dad, bad Dad,
go be someone else's dad.

461
00:23:23,370 --> 00:23:25,090
You're not my dad anymore.

462
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:26,689
Yuanyuan! Yuanyuan!

463
00:23:32,090 --> 00:23:34,130
Little fool, daring to go against me?

464
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:59,170
He's my dad, not yours.

465
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:14,529
What happened, Yuanyuan?

466
00:24:17,009 --> 00:24:17,810
What's going on?

467
00:24:18,249 --> 00:24:23,449
I got up for a drink, and Xiaofei
pushed me down from behind.

468
00:24:23,810 --> 00:24:24,850
He even hit me.

469
00:24:24,850 --> 00:24:25,489
Who hit you?

470
00:24:25,489 --> 00:24:26,330
Why did you push her?

471
00:24:26,330 --> 00:24:27,449
- It's late now. What's this about?
- You did hit me.

472
00:24:27,449 --> 00:24:28,130
Who hit you?

473
00:24:28,130 --> 00:24:29,449
- What are you doing?
- I didn't hit her!

474
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:30,009
No.

475
00:24:30,009 --> 00:24:30,850
- Then why does she say you hit her?
- Who hit you?

476
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:31,576
You pushed...

477
00:24:31,850 --> 00:24:32,570
Who hit you?

478
00:24:32,729 --> 00:24:33,229
Stop.

479
00:24:33,489 --> 00:24:35,009
Why push him? How could you push him?

480
00:24:35,009 --> 00:24:35,570
Move away.

481
00:24:36,570 --> 00:24:39,610
Haven't you had enough?
Can I sleep or not?

482
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:44,856
Come on, Yuanyuan.

483
00:24:45,529 --> 00:24:46,850
Get up. Come on. Let me hold you.

484
00:24:49,289 --> 00:24:51,130
It's okay now. Let's go back.

485
00:24:51,729 --> 00:24:52,229
Let's go.

486
00:25:46,969 --> 00:25:48,930
Xiaofei didn't push her for no reason.

487
00:25:49,610 --> 00:25:51,032
She splashed water on my face.

488
00:25:51,768 --> 00:25:52,890
So he pushed her away.

489
00:26:03,209 --> 00:26:03,850
I understand.

490
00:26:07,610 --> 00:26:08,330
And then?

491
00:26:09,850 --> 00:26:11,090
Is understanding enough?

492
00:26:13,410 --> 00:26:16,330
Yuanyuan is leaving tomorrow.
Be aware of that.

493
00:26:23,449 --> 00:26:25,650
Last night, we hoped you'd come out
and take a look.

494
00:26:26,170 --> 00:26:26,930
But you didn't.

495
00:26:28,810 --> 00:26:31,570
Just because we're your children,
do we deserve to be hit?

496
00:26:34,209 --> 00:26:35,930
You can't even protect
your own children.

497
00:26:37,289 --> 00:26:38,570
What a pathetic mother you are.

498
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:02,170
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
These years,

499
00:27:03,049 --> 00:27:04,449
I've always regretted it.

500
00:27:06,570 --> 00:27:08,930
I should've backed up Xiaoming
that night.

501
00:27:10,330 --> 00:27:11,969
I shouldn't have let her get slapped.

502
00:27:12,930 --> 00:27:14,209
But just like you said,

503
00:27:14,890 --> 00:27:17,170
I couldn't be at ease
in someone else's house.

504
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:21,969
Xiaoming has blamed me for years,
and I have nothing to say.

505
00:27:23,209 --> 00:27:24,890
Xiaoming doesn't blame you.

506
00:27:26,410 --> 00:27:29,650
Deep down,
it's just a child's grievance.

507
00:27:30,969 --> 00:27:33,810
You keep confronting her head-on.

508
00:27:34,330 --> 00:27:35,769
Her grievances can't just dissipate.

509
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:39,489
Just wait until she comes back
next time.

510
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:41,049
No need to apologize.

511
00:27:42,130 --> 00:27:44,664
Don't argue. Just listen.

512
00:27:45,752 --> 00:27:49,969
If you really feel she's wronged,
maybe her grievances will be gone.

513
00:27:51,330 --> 00:27:53,130
I feel wronged too.

514
00:27:53,969 --> 00:27:56,729
Exactly. Otherwise, why am I here?

515
00:27:57,610 --> 00:28:01,729
I'm just someone dispatched to listen
to the princess' grievances.

516
00:28:04,570 --> 00:28:05,689
Starting now,

517
00:28:06,330 --> 00:28:09,009
you must tell me
everything that's bothering you.

518
00:28:10,249 --> 00:28:11,969
If you don't tell me right away,

519
00:28:13,170 --> 00:28:14,009
I'll get upset.

520
00:28:21,529 --> 00:28:22,810
I can do whatever you ask.

521
00:28:23,529 --> 00:28:26,170
But there's one thing
you must listen to me about.

522
00:28:26,650 --> 00:28:27,289
What is it?

523
00:28:31,610 --> 00:28:32,650
Last time the doctor said,

524
00:28:33,650 --> 00:28:35,810
that you've got a bit of inflammation.

525
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:40,769
You must go to the hospital
for a checkup regularly, understand?

526
00:28:48,449 --> 00:28:50,610
Where did the time go?

527
00:28:53,529 --> 00:28:57,090
It all got stolen in a blink.

528
00:28:58,529 --> 00:28:59,810
Don't lose track of that clue.

529
00:29:01,170 --> 00:29:03,570
Captain Li, Yunli University
has sent Zhou Yun's records.

530
00:29:04,914 --> 00:29:06,982
(Yunli University Registration Form
Zhou Yun)

531
00:29:07,224 --> 00:29:08,216
We need to verify it.

532
00:29:08,489 --> 00:29:08,989
Alright.

533
00:29:13,009 --> 00:29:13,890
This isn't Ms. Zhou.

534
00:29:15,009 --> 00:29:15,890
Take a closer look.

535
00:29:16,289 --> 00:29:18,969
Is the photo too youthful,
different from what you remember?

536
00:29:20,209 --> 00:29:21,410
There's no way I can be wrong.

537
00:29:23,489 --> 00:29:26,489
When did you last hear news
about Ms. Zhou?

538
00:29:26,744 --> 00:29:27,800
First year of high school.

539
00:29:29,209 --> 00:29:31,689
That year, Ren Xiaoming and I
went back to find Ms. Zhou.

540
00:29:32,610 --> 00:29:33,110
(Qidaohezi, 2005)
May I come in?

541
00:29:33,249 --> 00:29:33,810
Come in.

542
00:29:35,810 --> 00:29:36,610
Hello, Ms. Liu.

543
00:29:36,952 --> 00:29:37,650
Hello, Ms. Liu.

544
00:29:37,850 --> 00:29:40,610
Bai Shu, Ren Xiaoming,
why are you two back?

545
00:29:41,969 --> 00:29:43,249
We came to see Ms. Zhou.

546
00:29:44,170 --> 00:29:46,570
Ms. Zhou? She was transferred.

547
00:29:47,930 --> 00:29:48,529
Transferred?

548
00:29:50,729 --> 00:29:51,650
Where to?

549
00:29:52,330 --> 00:29:54,890
I really don't know.
She left quite suddenly.

550
00:29:55,489 --> 00:29:57,090
Do you have her contact information?

551
00:29:57,449 --> 00:29:58,130
No.

552
00:29:58,410 --> 00:30:00,449
She doesn't have a phone.
No one can reach her.

553
00:30:05,410 --> 00:30:08,209
That was the last time
we had news about Ms. Zhou.

554
00:30:09,489 --> 00:30:13,009
Over the years, I've occasionally asked
some classmates and teachers about her.

555
00:30:13,729 --> 00:30:15,049
No one's heard from her.

556
00:30:16,170 --> 00:30:19,289
Oh, right. I was too busy a while ago
and forgot to tell you.

557
00:30:19,729 --> 00:30:24,489
I went to Qingzhou to see Xiaoming.
She asked me to pass a message to you.

558
00:30:25,529 --> 00:30:28,449
In this world, things aren't
as you say they are.

559
00:30:29,570 --> 00:30:30,769
You need evidence.

560
00:30:31,529 --> 00:30:33,610
Even if you say you have evidence,
she's not afraid.

561
00:30:34,090 --> 00:30:35,449
She won't concede to you on this.

562
00:30:36,209 --> 00:30:37,729
Her exact words. I'm not making it up.

563
00:30:38,410 --> 00:30:41,209
So, she doesn't admit
that the diary exists.

564
00:30:42,850 --> 00:30:43,410
Yeah.

565
00:30:43,850 --> 00:30:46,810
She's lying.
The diary is definitely with her.

566
00:30:49,489 --> 00:30:50,769
Can you help me get it back?

567
00:30:52,249 --> 00:30:53,249
How could I get it back?

568
00:30:53,489 --> 00:30:55,249
Besides, even if there
really is a diary,

569
00:30:56,009 --> 00:30:59,969
it is a civil dispute. What grounds do I
have to ask Xiaoming to bring it out?

570
00:31:01,729 --> 00:31:02,890
Did you finish the novel?

571
00:31:03,209 --> 00:31:05,090
Too busy lately.
So I just read the beginning.

572
00:31:05,489 --> 00:31:06,610
Then finish the novel.

573
00:31:06,850 --> 00:31:08,209
Sure, I'll read it when I can.

574
00:31:08,209 --> 00:31:09,930
No, you have to read it.

575
00:31:11,689 --> 00:31:14,410
What's up with you? Why so adamant
about me reading the novel?

576
00:31:15,610 --> 00:31:18,209
You want me to testify
that you had a hand in the novel?

577
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:21,529
Who asked you to testify?
I'm just asking you to read the novel.

578
00:31:24,689 --> 00:31:26,729
I'm going to be late. Goodbye.

579
00:31:32,729 --> 00:31:34,610
(The diary and the novel.)

580
00:31:35,410 --> 00:31:37,049
(Not getting along with Ren Xiaoming?)

581
00:31:43,449 --> 00:31:44,330
I'm on my way.

582
00:31:44,689 --> 00:31:47,249
Time to head out. The hearing starts
at 9:30. Don't be late.

583
00:31:47,689 --> 00:31:48,570
I know. I'll make it.

584
00:31:49,529 --> 00:31:50,570
What do you know?

585
00:31:51,650 --> 00:31:52,769
There's a lead on Wen Yuxiu.

586
00:31:53,570 --> 00:31:54,810
I'll tell you when we meet.

587
00:31:55,249 --> 00:31:58,009
A civilian search organization
found a Wen family in Qidaohezi.

588
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,728
There's a Wen Yuxiu
who might be the one you're looking for.

589
00:32:00,890 --> 00:32:02,570
I'll send you the photo and address.

590
00:32:20,449 --> 00:32:23,330
(Liang Yi, help me
postpone the court hearing.)

591
00:32:23,704 --> 00:32:25,049
(It's life or death. I must go.)

592
00:32:25,289 --> 00:32:25,969
(Ren Xiaoming,)

593
00:32:26,370 --> 00:32:28,410
I am Zhou Yun, your homeroom teacher.

594
00:32:29,650 --> 00:32:32,810
(You possess a truly rare quality
in your writing.)

595
00:32:33,130 --> 00:32:34,170
It's honesty.

596
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:39,769
(Your foundation is quite solid.)

597
00:32:40,610 --> 00:32:43,009
Would you like to strive hard
to get into Yucai?

598
00:32:58,130 --> 00:32:58,936
(My Dream)

599
00:33:00,018 --> 00:33:00,728
(Face yourself. Always be honest.)

600
00:33:02,249 --> 00:33:04,410
(The Voyage of the Beagle)
(I have always hoped to hear from her.)

601
00:33:05,410 --> 00:33:08,850
(But I never thought she'd come back
into my life like this.)

602
00:33:18,850 --> 00:33:19,570
Found Zhou Yun?

603
00:33:19,689 --> 00:33:23,570
The Zhou Yun matching the records
owns a building materials factory.

604
00:33:23,850 --> 00:33:26,850
We checked her background.
She has never worked as a teacher.

605
00:33:27,330 --> 00:33:29,170
Based on various information,
we can confirm

606
00:33:29,449 --> 00:33:32,969
that the Qidian Middle School Zhou Yun
impersonated the factory owner.

607
00:33:37,249 --> 00:33:41,090
Hello, Ms. Zhou. I'm Li Meng, detective
from the Criminal Investigation Unit.

608
00:33:41,209 --> 00:33:44,529
This is my colleague Huang Yue.
We are here to ask you a few questions.

609
00:33:44,810 --> 00:33:46,289
(Public Security)
Here's our police ID.

610
00:33:48,610 --> 00:33:49,289
Please sit.

611
00:33:52,410 --> 00:33:52,910
Thank you.

612
00:33:56,449 --> 00:33:58,249
I need to state in advance,

613
00:33:58,449 --> 00:34:01,890
that due to our regulations,
this conversation needs to be recorded.

614
00:34:03,529 --> 00:34:04,170
Go ahead.

615
00:34:08,449 --> 00:34:10,210
What do you want
to investigate, officers?

616
00:34:11,129 --> 00:34:13,969
We suspect someone
has been using your identity.

617
00:34:14,609 --> 00:34:16,890
It's not unauthorized use.
I lent it to her myself.

618
00:34:19,449 --> 00:34:20,049
Ms. Zhou,

619
00:34:21,129 --> 00:34:24,459
did you know that lending
your identity to others is illegal?

620
00:34:24,459 --> 00:34:25,089
I know.

621
00:34:25,609 --> 00:34:26,850
For lending ID documents,

622
00:34:26,850 --> 00:34:30,330
Public Security will impose a warning
and a fine of less than 200 yuan.

623
00:34:30,810 --> 00:34:31,690
I accept the penalty.

624
00:34:32,529 --> 00:34:34,449
Ms. Zhou, that's not all.

625
00:34:35,290 --> 00:34:37,630
If the person using your identity
has broken the law,

626
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:39,969
you must also bear
the corresponding legal responsibility.

627
00:34:42,049 --> 00:34:43,009
What did she do?

628
00:34:44,449 --> 00:34:45,489
She disappeared.

629
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:47,290
Disappeared?

630
00:34:49,449 --> 00:34:50,649
Huang, the photo.

631
00:34:56,489 --> 00:34:59,559
Please see if this is the pen

632
00:34:59,559 --> 00:35:02,009
you customized
at Shanghai Gold Pen Store in 1991.

633
00:35:05,969 --> 00:35:07,409
Where did you find it?

634
00:35:07,409 --> 00:35:10,930
We found this pen
next to a woman's corpse.

635
00:35:12,449 --> 00:35:13,089
Woman's corpse?

636
00:35:15,089 --> 00:35:16,569
I gave her this pen.

637
00:35:20,169 --> 00:35:21,049
She died?

638
00:35:23,489 --> 00:35:26,529
We suspect this corpse is Zhou Yun...

639
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:29,489
The person you lent your ID to.

640
00:35:30,009 --> 00:35:32,089
That's why we've come to investigate.

641
00:35:34,449 --> 00:35:36,449
Since you could lend her your identity,

642
00:35:37,129 --> 00:35:39,210
it indicates
that you two were quite close.

643
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:43,529
I suppose you'd really like
to know the truth too, right?

644
00:35:44,290 --> 00:35:47,169
So please tell us who exactly she is.

645
00:36:08,649 --> 00:36:12,330
I really don't know
that skinny girl's real name.

646
00:36:13,649 --> 00:36:16,049
That was the winter of 1992.

647
00:36:17,810 --> 00:36:18,890
It was around the New Year.

648
00:36:20,210 --> 00:36:21,969
Lots of workers went home.

649
00:36:31,346 --> 00:36:35,169
(Suburban Building Materials Factory
Qidaohezi, 1992)

650
00:36:35,169 --> 00:36:39,850
♪Roses, roses, so dazzling♪

651
00:36:40,489 --> 00:36:41,930
Open the door!

652
00:36:49,009 --> 00:36:51,449
She was completely frozen stiff.

653
00:36:52,129 --> 00:36:53,770
I thought she was dead.

654
00:36:59,210 --> 00:37:00,049
You're alive?

655
00:37:01,489 --> 00:37:05,250
Help! Someone help!

656
00:37:07,529 --> 00:37:10,009
Get up. Oh, my.

657
00:37:11,770 --> 00:37:13,089
Someone help!

658
00:37:16,649 --> 00:37:17,449
What's wrong, Madam?

659
00:37:17,529 --> 00:37:19,449
- Get up. Come on.
- Hurry.

660
00:37:21,569 --> 00:37:22,850
Hold her up.

661
00:37:31,609 --> 00:37:35,330
When she woke up,
she didn't know her own name.

662
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:39,649
She begged me to let her stay
and work in the factory.

663
00:38:05,489 --> 00:38:06,969
(It was almost the New Year.)

664
00:38:07,370 --> 00:38:11,649
(She could do the work
of two men on her own,)

665
00:38:13,489 --> 00:38:16,129
(and she only took half the pay.)

666
00:38:24,129 --> 00:38:25,529
(She was so well-behaved.)

667
00:38:26,089 --> 00:38:28,089
Who cared what her name was?

668
00:38:28,890 --> 00:38:30,089
She was so skinny.

669
00:38:30,489 --> 00:38:33,969
Everyone in the factory
just called her "Skinny."

670
00:38:44,449 --> 00:38:45,169
Madam.

671
00:38:45,969 --> 00:38:48,609
It's holiday time.
You haven't gone home?

672
00:38:49,009 --> 00:38:49,969
Not going out for fun?

673
00:38:50,210 --> 00:38:52,890
It's fine. I'll clean all these shoes.

674
00:38:55,649 --> 00:39:01,009
You work with all the men and never
lose out. You're so strong-willed.

675
00:39:03,449 --> 00:39:06,810
I've taken your wages.
It's only right to do this work.

676
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:10,969
What's your education?

677
00:39:13,009 --> 00:39:13,850
Teachers' college.

678
00:39:15,890 --> 00:39:17,210
I've got a bachelor's degree.

679
00:39:19,649 --> 00:39:22,609
I was the only female college student
in our village.

680
00:39:23,890 --> 00:39:25,009
You're really amazing.

681
00:39:27,569 --> 00:39:28,890
Just the year I graduated,

682
00:39:29,890 --> 00:39:30,930
my dad passed away.

683
00:39:31,569 --> 00:39:34,609
My brother was getting older,
and the family was extremely poor.

684
00:39:34,609 --> 00:39:35,690
He couldn't find a wife.

685
00:39:36,489 --> 00:39:38,129
I married my husband.

686
00:39:38,529 --> 00:39:40,690
Now I'm the boss lady of this factory.

687
00:39:43,449 --> 00:39:44,890
I'll tell you honestly.

688
00:39:45,569 --> 00:39:48,489
My dream is to become a teacher,

689
00:39:49,890 --> 00:39:51,049
standing on the podium,

690
00:39:51,049 --> 00:39:52,850
and wearing a white shirt
and blue pants,

691
00:39:53,569 --> 00:39:55,730
just like clouds in the blue sky.

692
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:00,169
Oh, right. I had a dream
the night before last.

693
00:40:00,489 --> 00:40:03,529
I dreamt of actually
standing on the podium.

694
00:40:04,169 --> 00:40:07,770
I said, "Everyone, stand up!"

695
00:40:12,169 --> 00:40:13,330
And then, I woke up.

696
00:40:15,049 --> 00:40:17,169
I didn't hear anyone call me teacher.

697
00:40:25,489 --> 00:40:26,730
Actually, my dream

698
00:40:28,089 --> 00:40:30,489
is also to become an honorable teacher.

699
00:40:33,290 --> 00:40:34,169
What did you say?

700
00:40:37,770 --> 00:40:38,370
Girl,

701
00:40:40,049 --> 00:40:40,850
say it again.

702
00:40:42,210 --> 00:40:43,609
I also want to be a teacher.

703
00:40:47,129 --> 00:40:47,690
Come on.

704
00:40:54,649 --> 00:40:58,089
We're like-minded. I really cherish you.

705
00:40:58,449 --> 00:40:59,949
Stop what you're doing. Let's go.

706
00:41:00,049 --> 00:41:01,890
Let's go chat at my place. Hurry.

707
00:41:02,850 --> 00:41:05,890
Look at your hands. Such small hands.
How tender they are!

708
00:41:05,890 --> 00:41:07,830
It makes me worried. Let's go.

709
00:41:09,529 --> 00:41:11,690
I found that you're just like me.

710
00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:14,009
If there's anything, just talk to me.

711
00:41:16,169 --> 00:41:20,449
She was the only one in the factory
who can chat with me.

712
00:41:20,529 --> 00:41:21,370
Just chatting.

713
00:41:22,569 --> 00:41:24,930
She was a soulmate of mine.

714
00:41:25,770 --> 00:41:28,370
(If only life were as it was
at first sight.)

715
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:30,730
(Building Materials Factory, 1995)
Why does the autumn wind sadden the fan?

716
00:41:31,290 --> 00:41:33,850
The brocade zither
has 50 strings for no reason.

717
00:41:34,890 --> 00:41:37,250
Each string and column reminisce
about flourishing years.

718
00:41:37,449 --> 00:41:40,330
A bamboo cane and straw shoes
easily surpass a horse.

719
00:41:41,129 --> 00:41:41,730
Who is afraid?

720
00:41:43,370 --> 00:41:46,290
In a cloak amidst misty rain,
live one's life freely.

721
00:41:53,930 --> 00:41:54,730
I'm leaving.

722
00:41:57,449 --> 00:41:58,049
Where to?

723
00:41:58,370 --> 00:41:59,169
Haven't decided yet.

724
00:42:00,210 --> 00:42:02,330
I've saved up a little money. Not much,

725
00:42:02,969 --> 00:42:04,609
but it's enough to live on for a while.

726
00:42:05,730 --> 00:42:08,089
I need to get out.
I can't stay trapped here.

727
00:42:10,290 --> 00:42:14,330
Girl, I want to go with you.
Take me with you.

728
00:42:19,730 --> 00:42:22,930
(I don't even have an identity.
And I don't know where I can go yet.)

729
00:42:25,649 --> 00:42:26,609
Fine, let's go together.

730
00:42:27,810 --> 00:42:29,089
While we're still young.

731
00:42:33,330 --> 00:42:38,529
Haven't you seen in the grand hall,
the bright mirror mourns the white hair?

732
00:42:39,609 --> 00:42:42,609
In the morning it's like black hair,
and by evening it turns to snow.

733
00:42:43,930 --> 00:42:46,930
Give up splendid horses and costly furs.

734
00:42:47,690 --> 00:42:51,569
Call the children
to exchange for fine wine.

735
00:42:53,330 --> 00:42:55,690
- Let us dissipate
- Let us dissipate

736
00:42:56,250 --> 00:42:58,210
- eternal sorrow together.
- eternal sorrow together.

737
00:42:59,370 --> 00:43:00,089
It's a deal!

738
00:43:01,169 --> 00:43:01,810
Cheers!

739
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
